commit.message:
Remove redundant wheel dep from pyproject.toml

Remove the redundant `wheel` dependency, as it is added by the backend
automatically.  Listing it explicitly in the documentation was
a historical mistake and has been fixed since, see:
https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/commit/f7d30a9529378cf69054b5176249e5457aaf640a
Require a current version of Python

Revert breaking API changes

This reverts the following commits:
- 7fc7eef9991cce890795ff1aa237bd2d1e456c9d
- 29a5499b2f2cf9c9a4a3ec9de4d40a6b421a0ab8
- 45c53b40609f205f7328ce173de8e3405430a3d0
Improve names of private parsing functions

Use phony targets in Makefile

Also add a few more files to clean.
Add type hints to integration test decorator

Polish error handling

Add BuriedWithJobIDError to differentiate with BuriedError (which
contains no ID) and improve usage with type checking.

Document error attributes and reorder documentation to list more common
errors first.
Document and type hint Job attributes

Remove sphinx-autodoc-typehints dev dependency

This feature is included in Sphinx now.

Always use bytes for job bodies

This is a breaking change that removes the automatic string encoding and
decoding when a Client's encoding is not None. Although convenient, it
doesn't play nice with type hints and overall doesn't seem worth the
API complexity.

From mypy's documentation on Union types:

> This also means that it's recommended to avoid union types as
> function return types, since the caller may have to use isinstance()
> before doing anything interesting with the value.
Make it clear the requirements are for development
Add command for building HTML docs
Update link after changing default branch to main
